description.narrative: Progress was made on C4D evidence generation through the completion of a WASH Knowledge Attitude Practices study which contributed to improved C4D planning and implementation. The WASH KAP integrated nutrition, health and education aspects relevant to C4D. Progress was also made in developing C4D capacity among subnational health workers in social mobilization and in developing budgeted strategies as well as community mobilization on key behaviours. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:17/01/2020
